                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_109253">Drayton</placeName>.<lb/>
      (i) <hi rend="italic">Various grants.</hi>

   Agreement by which <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Fers</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName> appoints <persName>
                           <forename>Agnes</forename> daughter of <persName>
                              <forename>Ralph</forename> le <surname>Coupere</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName> as his heir, to have at his death (i) two messuages in <placeName key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>; one between the tenements of <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> the <surname>tailor (<hi rend="italic">sartor</hi>)</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Fers</surname>
                        </persName>, the other between the messuages of <persName>
                           <forename>Adam</forename> le <surname>Waller</surname>
                        </persName> and the said John; (ii) lands to the amount of ½ ... in <placeName key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName> above H[...]rdys by the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename> de <surname>aula</surname>
                        </persName>, and a rood above <placeName key="place_108152">Drayton Mawelond</placeName>, on condition that she shall serve him faithfully to the end of his life, and pay 2/- to the chief lord of the fee. 
   Witnesses: <persName>... <surname>le Werrour</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Symon</forename> de <surname>Aula</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Symon</forename> 
                           <surname>Baudewyne</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Jordan</forename> 
                           <surname>William</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Scop</surname>
                        </persName>. [<hi rend="italic">Mutilated.</hi>]
   <origDate notBefore="1290" notAfter="1300" precision="low">
                           <supplied>c. 1290–1300.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
